======================
OLED C Click Board
======================

OLED C click can display up to 65K/262K different colors and shades on a compact size display, based on the OLED technology.
It provides better power consumption, better picture quality, better response times and more

=================
Key features
=================
* OLED C click is equipped with the 96x96 high-color OLED display
* Very good brightness-to-contrast ratio, does not require any backlight - since the pixel elements emit light on their own
* Better angle of viewing - compared to traditional TFT screens
* Interfaces:SPI
* 3.3v power supply

==================
INTERFACE SETTINGS
==================
The MCU connects to the SPI pins of the LCD MINI click board.

Interrupts: Only if drivers configured to use IRQs.


==================
Clickboard Example
==================

Example carries Displaying the Microchip Logo in oledC Display. 

===================
RUNNING THE EXAMPLE
===================
1. Add OLED C click component to application
2. Configure the corresponding I/O pins 
   * SPI: Add to run example, assign relevant pins.

3. Export Project: Name and download to relevant IDE. 
4. In Atmel Studio 7: File->Import->Atmel Start Project.
5. In main.c: 
   
   * In main, while(1) loop call: oledC_example()(./examples/src/click_example.c)
   * Add related headerfile:#include<click_example.h>(./examples/include/click_example.h)
   
6. Build and flash into supported evaluation board.
